n gold medal winner Adrienne Titmus but keeping a healthy distance between herself and the other competitors.\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 577, \"end\": 587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9956468188101696, \"rank\": 0.004272847672852448, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 615, \"end\": 621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite being just 17 years old, this is McIntosh's second time at the Olympics, as she was also a part of the Canadian team at the Toyko 2020 Olympics at just 14.\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 738, \"end\": 746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999999629381, \"rank\": 3.690208878569485e-11, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 808, \"end\": 816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9996910067782182, \"rank\": 0.0002885005078381233, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 835, \"end\": 848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0662279630126664e-17, \"text\": \"2020 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She nearly won a medal then, as well, placing fourth in the 400m free.\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 931, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She holds the world record in the women's 400 individual medley, which she will participate in on Monday.\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 1038, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh finished today's race with an extremely impressive time of 3:58.37, while Titmus was just slightly ahead at 3:57.49.\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1040, \"end\": 1048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999999629381, \"rank\": 3.690208878569485e-11, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 1123, \"end\": 1129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Placing third was American swimmer Katie Ledecky, who finished with a time of 4:00.86.\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9992563591608373, \"rank\": 0.0007387080873500306, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1201, \"end\": 1214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.or